cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically the problem of separating multiple illuminants in a single image. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep neural networks for training, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper incorporates intuitions from the physics of image formation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper deals with image-based separation algorithms, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
